[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":616},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2021\u002F01\u002F16\u002Flearn-vim-in-vscode-quick-start\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2021\u002F01\u002F16\u002Flearn-vim-in-vscode-quick-start\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2021\u002F01\u002F16\u002Flearn-vim-in-vscode-quick-start\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2021\u002F01\u002F16\u002Flearn-vim-in-vscode-quick-start\u002F":592,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2021\u002F01\u002F16\u002Flearn-vim-in-vscode-quick-start\u002F":601},"\u002Fvscode\u002F20210116\u002F2465721796\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":574,"date":575,"description":576,"extension":577,"lang":578,"meta":579,"navigation":580,"path":581,"readingMinutes":582,"seo":583,"standalone":584,"stem":585,"tags":586,"tldr":589,"updated":575,"url":590,"__hash__":591},"content\u002Fen\u002FVSCode\u002Flearn-vim-in-vscode-quick-start.md","Learn Vim in 10 Minutes With VSCode (Beginner Walkthrough)","9077894283",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":562},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,27,36,39,42,45,49,52,88,91,98,105,109,126,132,189,197,201,204,245,251,257,263,275,281,285,288,295,301,304,355,358,362,372,378,381,387,390,433,439,442,490,495,502,505,546,555,559],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"This is a Vim beginner walkthrough. Fair warning — you'll definitely hit walls early on. The concept is actually pretty close to learning a new input method.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"installing-the-extension","Installing the extension",[17,25,26],{},"The fastest way to get used to Vim is to switch your existing editor into Vim mode, so install this extension first:",[17,28,29],{},[30,31,35],"a",{"href":32,"rel":33},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=vscodevim.vim",[34],"nofollow","VSCode Vim extension",[17,37,38],{},"(I'm using VSCode to write this.)",[17,40,41],{},"Once installed, if you've never touched Vim before, you'll feel like a complete beginner — so this post is a basic walkthrough.",[17,43,44],{},"This walkthrough is based on the VSCode extension, so a few things might differ slightly from real Vim, but in my experience it's pretty close. Maybe because I've used Vim a bit before.",[12,46,48],{"id":47},"modes","Modes",[17,50,51],{},"Vim has four basic modes:",[53,54,55,64,72,80],"ul",{},[56,57,58,59],"li",{},"Normal mode\n",[53,60,61],{},[56,62,63],{},"Also called the default mode.",[56,65,66,67],{},"Insert mode\n",[53,68,69],{},[56,70,71],{},"Also called the input mode — text-typing mode.",[56,73,74,75],{},"Visual mode\n",[53,76,77],{},[56,78,79],{},"Used for selecting text or highlighting for emphasis. Personally I mostly use it for selecting.",[56,81,82,83,87],{},"Command mode (start with ",[84,85,86],"code",{},":",")",[17,89,90],{},"When you switch modes, the bottom of VSCode shows you which mode you're in.",[17,92,93],{},[94,95],"img",{"alt":96,"src":97},"Mode indicator (happened to be listening to music)","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002FJavaScript%20%E6%A0%B8%E5%BF%83%E8%A7%80%E5%BF%B5\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202021-01-16%2012.04.21.png",[17,99,100,101,104],{},"A lot of actions only work in specific modes. The most common newbie problem is \"I don't know how to get out of this mode.\" Easy — press ",[84,102,103],{},"ESC"," and you're back in Normal mode.",[12,106,108],{"id":107},"moving-around-normal-mode","Moving around (Normal mode)",[17,110,111,112,115,116,115,119,115,122,125],{},"Normally you'd move with the arrow keys. In Vim, you stay in Normal mode and use ",[84,113,114],{},"h",", ",[84,117,118],{},"j",[84,120,121],{},"k",[84,123,124],{},"l"," to move (arrow keys still work too, no judgement).",[17,127,128,129,131],{},"(If you're not sure which mode you're in, just spam ",[84,130,103],{},".)",[133,134,135,149],"table",{},[136,137,138],"thead",{},[139,140,141,146],"tr",{},[142,143,145],"th",{"align":144},"center","Key",[142,147,148],{"align":144},"What it does",[150,151,152,162,171,180],"tbody",{},[139,153,154,159],{},[155,156,157],"td",{"align":144},[84,158,114],{},[155,160,161],{"align":144},"Move left one character",[139,163,164,168],{},[155,165,166],{"align":144},[84,167,118],{},[155,169,170],{"align":144},"Move down one line",[139,172,173,177],{},[155,174,175],{"align":144},[84,176,121],{},[155,178,179],{"align":144},"Move up one line",[139,181,182,186],{},[155,183,184],{"align":144},[84,185,124],{},[155,187,188],{"align":144},"Move right one character",[17,190,191,192,196],{},"Note: ",[193,194,195],"strong",{},"case matters",".",[12,198,200],{"id":199},"insert-mode","Insert mode",[17,202,203],{},"Once you've moved the cursor where you want it, you'll want to start typing. That means entering Insert mode. There are four ways:",[133,205,206,214],{},[136,207,208],{},[139,209,210,212],{},[142,211,145],{"align":144},[142,213,148],{"align":144},[150,215,216,226,235],{},[139,217,218,223],{},[155,219,220],{"align":144},[84,221,222],{},"i",[155,224,225],{"align":144},"Enter Insert mode before the cursor",[139,227,228,232],{},[155,229,230],{"align":144},[84,231,30],{},[155,233,234],{"align":144},"Enter Insert mode after the cursor",[139,236,237,242],{},[155,238,239],{"align":144},[84,240,241],{},"o",[155,243,244],{"align":144},"Open a new line below and enter Insert mode",[17,246,247],{},[94,248],{"alt":249,"src":250},"Press i","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002FJavaScript%20%E6%A0%B8%E5%BF%83%E8%A7%80%E5%BF%B5\u002F%E8%9E%A2%E5%B9%95%E9%8C%84%E8%A3%BD%202021-01-16%2012.36.20.gif",[17,252,253],{},[94,254],{"alt":255,"src":256},"Press a","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002FJavaScript%20%E6%A0%B8%E5%BF%83%E8%A7%80%E5%BF%B5\u002F%E8%9E%A2%E5%B9%95%E9%8C%84%E8%A3%BD%202021-01-16%2012.36.31.gif",[17,258,259],{},[94,260],{"alt":261,"src":262},"Press o","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002FJavaScript%20%E6%A0%B8%E5%BF%83%E8%A7%80%E5%BF%B5\u002F%E8%9E%A2%E5%B9%95%E9%8C%84%E8%A3%BD%202021-01-16%2012.36.55.gif",[17,264,265,266,268,269,271,272,274],{},"Exit Insert mode with ",[84,267,103],{}," (as always — if you want to exit anything, just spam ",[84,270,103],{},"). I'd also recommend building the habit of hitting ",[84,273,103],{}," after every action, otherwise you'll end up in the classic situation:",[276,277,278],"blockquote",{},[17,279,280],{},"I've been learning Vim for ages and I still don't know how to exit. (lol)",[12,282,284],{"id":283},"selecting-copying-pasting-visual-mode","Selecting, copying, pasting (Visual mode)",[17,286,287],{},"Now the basics — select, copy, paste. You could fall back to the standard Ctrl + C \u002F V, but you're using Vim now, you might as well commit.",[17,289,290,291,294],{},"Enter Visual mode by pressing ",[84,292,293],{},"v",". The cursor doesn't look any different visually, but the moment you use the arrow keys you'll see text being selected.",[17,296,297],{},[94,298],{"alt":299,"src":300},"Visual mode","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002FJavaScript%20%E6%A0%B8%E5%BF%83%E8%A7%80%E5%BF%B5\u002Fezgif.com-gif-maker.gif",[17,302,303],{},"Once in Visual mode:",[133,305,306,314],{},[136,307,308],{},[139,309,310,312],{},[142,311,145],{"align":144},[142,313,148],{"align":144},[150,315,316,326,335,345],{},[139,317,318,323],{},[155,319,320],{"align":144},[84,321,322],{},"y",[155,324,325],{"align":144},"Copy (yank) selected text",[139,327,328,332],{},[155,329,330],{"align":144},[84,331,17],{},[155,333,334],{"align":144},"Paste the last copied text",[139,336,337,342],{},[155,338,339],{"align":144},[84,340,341],{},"d",[155,343,344],{"align":144},"Cut (delete) selected text",[139,346,347,352],{},[155,348,349],{"align":144},[84,350,351],{},"u",[155,353,354],{"align":144},"Undo the last action (e.g. delete or cut)",[17,356,357],{},"Reminder: case still matters.",[12,359,361],{"id":360},"movement-tricks","Movement tricks",[17,363,364,365,368,369,196],{},"Vim has a really fun command-mode feature for jumping to a specific line number, which I love. Say you're 100+ lines into a file and need to jump to line 1. Press ",[84,366,367],{},"Shift + :"," and the bottom bar shows ",[84,370,371],{},":|",[17,373,374],{},[94,375],{"alt":376,"src":377},"Command mode prompt","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002FJavaScript%20%E6%A0%B8%E5%BF%83%E8%A7%80%E5%BF%B5\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202021-01-16%2015.59.09.png",[17,379,380],{},"Type the line number, hit Enter, and you jump there.",[17,382,383],{},[94,384],{"alt":385,"src":386},"Jump to line","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002FJavaScript%20%E6%A0%B8%E5%BF%83%E8%A7%80%E5%BF%B5\u002Fn08tb-armte(1).gif",[17,388,389],{},"You might want a faster way to jump to the top or bottom of the file without typing commands:",[133,391,392,400],{},[136,393,394],{},[139,395,396,398],{},[142,397,145],{"align":144},[142,399,148],{"align":144},[150,401,402,416],{},[139,403,404,409],{},[155,405,406],{"align":144},[84,407,408],{},"gg",[155,410,411,412,415],{"align":144},"Jump to the first line of the current window (press ",[84,413,414],{},"g"," twice — like saying \"gg\" in a game when you've died and need to restart)",[139,417,418,423],{},[155,419,420],{"align":144},[84,421,422],{},"Shift + g",[155,424,425,426,428,429,432],{"align":144},"Jump to the last line (with Shift, ",[84,427,414],{}," becomes uppercase ",[84,430,431],{},"G"," — I'm using lowercase in the table to show the keystroke)",[17,434,435,436,196],{},"Note: both of these only work in ",[193,437,438],{},"Normal mode",[17,440,441],{},"You might also want to jump to the start or end of the current line (not the window). Three ways:",[133,443,444,452],{},[136,445,446],{},[139,447,448,450],{},[142,449,145],{"align":144},[142,451,148],{"align":144},[150,453,454,470,480],{},[139,455,456,461],{},[155,457,458],{"align":144},[84,459,460],{},"0",[155,462,463,464,466,467,87],{"align":144},"Jump to the start of the line (the digit ",[84,465,460],{},", not the letter ",[84,468,469],{},"O",[139,471,472,477],{},[155,473,474],{"align":144},[84,475,476],{},"Shift + 6 (^)",[155,478,479],{"align":144},"Jump to the start of the line",[139,481,482,487],{},[155,483,484],{"align":144},[84,485,486],{},"Shift + 4 ($)",[155,488,489],{"align":144},"Jump to the end of the line",[17,491,492,493,196],{},"All three require ",[193,494,438],{},[17,496,497,498,501],{},"One last navigation trick — search. Press ",[84,499,500],{},"\u002F"," to enter search mode, then type what you want to find (English only, no Chinese).",[17,503,504],{},"After typing, press Enter to commit the search. If the result isn't quite what you wanted, use these to jump between matches:",[133,506,507,515],{},[136,508,509],{},[139,510,511,513],{},[142,512,145],{"align":144},[142,514,148],{"align":144},[150,516,517,526,536],{},[139,518,519,523],{},[155,520,521],{"align":144},[84,522,500],{},[155,524,525],{"align":144},"Enter search mode (English only, press Enter to confirm)",[139,527,528,533],{},[155,529,530],{"align":144},[84,531,532],{},"Shift + 8 (*)",[155,534,535],{"align":144},"Jump to next match",[139,537,538,543],{},[155,539,540],{"align":144},[84,541,542],{},"Shift + 3 (#)",[155,544,545],{"align":144},"Jump to previous match",[17,547,548,549,551,552,554],{},"Found what you wanted? Press ",[84,550,222],{}," or ",[84,553,30],{}," to drop into Insert mode.",[12,556,558],{"id":557},"wrapping-up","Wrapping up",[17,560,561],{},"Vim genuinely has a learning curve at the start. This post is just a basic intro — there are a ton of more advanced tricks I haven't covered. If you've ever learned an alphabet-key input method like Boshiamy, you'll recognise the feeling: \"wow there are a lot of key roots to memorise.\" Vim is the same. But once you're comfortable, moving around to edit code or write articles becomes really fast.",{"title":563,"searchDepth":564,"depth":564,"links":565},"",2,[566,567,568,569,570,571,572,573],{"id":14,"depth":564,"text":15},{"id":22,"depth":564,"text":23},{"id":47,"depth":564,"text":48},{"id":107,"depth":564,"text":108},{"id":199,"depth":564,"text":200},{"id":283,"depth":564,"text":284},{"id":360,"depth":564,"text":361},{"id":557,"depth":564,"text":558},"VSCode","2021-01-16 11:42:06","A beginner walkthrough for Vim — fair warning, you'll definitely hit walls early on. The concept is honestly closer to learning a new input method than a new editor.","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002Flearn-vim-in-vscode-quick-start","4",{"title":6,"description":576},false,"en\u002FVSCode\u002Flearn-vim-in-vscode-quick-start",[574,587,588],"Vim","Vi",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2021\u002F01\u002F16\u002Flearn-vim-in-vscode-quick-start\u002F","zMiEgsiYHJoaqWQNB_MPFQlmpfxHM6tNzkpH9cr7Ipk",{"newer":593,"older":597},{"url":594,"title":595,"date":596},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2021\u002F01\u002F17\u002Fjavascript-core-47-prototype-chain-why-prototypes\u002F","JavaScript Core Concepts (47): Why Does JavaScript Even Have Prototypes?","2021-01-17 21:06:16",{"url":598,"title":599,"date":600},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2021\u002F01\u002F16\u002Fjavascript-core-46-functions-and-this-exercises\u002F","JavaScript Core Concepts (46): Functions and How This Works — Practice Quiz","2021-01-16 10:03:19",[602,607,612],{"url":603,"title":604,"date":605,"readingMinutes":606},"\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2025\u002F04\u002F24\u002Fvscode-cannot-find-git-set-git-path\u002F","VSCode 'Can't Find Git, Install It or Use git.path' — How to Fix","2025-04-24 09:52:23","1",{"url":608,"title":609,"date":610,"readingMinutes":611},"\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2024\u002F09\u002F08\u002Fgithub-copilot-tips-and-tricks-deep-dive\u002F","GitHub Copilot Feels Awkward? You Might Just Not Know These Tricks","2024-09-08 13:06:00","5",{"url":613,"title":614,"date":615,"readingMinutes":606},"\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2023\u002F10\u002F26\u002Fvscode-vue-custom-component-syntax-highlight-fix\u002F","Vue Custom Components Lost Their Highlighting in VSCode — Here's the Fix","2023-10-26 11:03:07",1784012792398]